cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image feature matching, which is a fundamental part of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses a Graph Convolutional Network to learn an appropriate embedding function, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also deals with unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. The paper also deals with geometric consistency losses, which falls under the category of computational geometry, making cs.GR (Computational Geometry) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with multiple images, which is a subfield of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
